Description: Cup with a slightly irregular plain rim, slightly inverted in places, and a rounded base; reddish-brown fabric discoloured to grey on one side, bands of rocker-stamped decoration randomly distributed across the vessel including the base, produced with several different rocker stamps. Handmade. Inomplete with complete profile.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Northern Dongola Reach, Site S10 Context 16
Type series: NDRS type C2.1 (published form type series number)
NDRS type D2.9 (published decoration type series number)

Acquisition notes: Division of finds from the National Corporation for Antiquities and Museums, Khartoum to SARS, the license holder.
